Xerces is required for installing GridLab-D.

It can be installed as an independent library.

These instructions were followed to install xerces version 3.2.0 on Linux Ubuntu dist.

1. $ wget http://mirror.metrocast.net/apache//xerces/c/3/sources/xerces-c-3.2.0.tar.gz
2. tar -xvzf xerces-c-3.2.0.tar.gz; cd  xerces-c-3.2.0
3. $ ./configure --disable-static CFLAGS=-O2 CXXFLAGS=-O2
4. $make; $ sudo make install

This will install xerces library in /usr/local/lib/

e.g.

$ ls -l /usr/local/lib/libxerces-c*
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 4736256 Feb 28 08:16 /usr//local/lib/libxerces-c-3.2.so
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root     949 Feb 28 08:16 /usr//local/lib/libxerces-c.la
lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root      18 Feb 28 08:16 /usr//local/lib/libxerces-c.so -> libxerces-c-3.2.so

For Mac OS X, installation should be similar.
